## 1. What’s New

### 1.1 Feature Summary

The ReAct tool-calling loop in Kiro Chat Panel now works correctly. Previously, when the AI assistant needed to use tools (read files, search code, etc.), the operation would fail with a 400 error after the first tool call. This patch fixes the underlying identifier mismatch that caused all tool continuations to break.

**User impact:** Developers using Kiro Chat Panel can now use multi-step tool-assisted conversations without interruption. The AI can chain multiple tool calls (read file → analyze → write file) in a single conversation turn.

### 1.2 User-Facing Changes

| # | Change | Description | Impact |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Tool calling restored | ReAct tool loop now completes without 400 errors | High |
| 2 | Better error messages | Tool continuation failures now show descriptive diagnostics instead of generic 400 | Medium |

## 2. Technical Changes

### 2.1 API Changes

| Type | Endpoint | Method | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Fixed | /chat/completions | POST | Tool continuation no longer returns 400 on valid requests |
| Improved | /chat/completions | POST | Mismatch errors now return structured error body with available\_ids |

### 2.2 Database Changes

No database changes. This fix is entirely in-memory.

### 2.3 Configuration Changes

No configuration changes required.

### 2.4 Infrastructure Changes

No infrastructure changes. Standard container redeploy.

## 3. Bug Fixes

| # | Jira Ticket | Summary | Severity |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | KSA-236 | tool\_use\_id mismatch between SSE stream and conversation history causes 400 on tool continuation | Critical |

**Root Cause:** The Anthropic converter (converter.ts) was generating NEW tool\_use\_id values when creating SSE events instead of passing through the original ID from the Kiro Q API response. This caused the extension to send back a toolUseId that didn’t match anything in kiro-ts conversation history.

**Fix:** Direct passthrough of block.id from API response to both SSE stream and history storage.

